WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.347
Etiologically, myocarditis is broadly classified into

00:00:03.347 --> 00:00:06.695
infectious, autoimmune, toxic, and vaccine-associated categories.

00:00:06.695 --> 00:00:10.042
Viruses account for the majority of

00:00:10.042 --> 00:00:13.389
cases — Coxsackievirus B historically, though

00:00:13.389 --> 00:00:16.737
SARS-CoV-2 has emerged as a significant

00:00:16.737 --> 00:00:17.295
cause.

00:00:17.295 --> 00:00:20.642
Autoimmune etiologies include giant cell myocarditis,

00:00:20.642 --> 00:00:23.432
cardiac sarcoidosis, and systemic lupus.

00:00:23.432 --> 00:00:26.779
Toxic causes encompass immune checkpoint inhibitors,

00:00:26.779 --> 00:00:28.453
anthracyclines, and clozapine.

00:00:28.453 --> 00:00:31.800
Vaccine-associated myocarditis — particularly following mRNA

00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:35.147
COVID-19 vaccination — is now well-characterized,

00:00:35.147 --> 00:00:38.495
predominantly affecting males aged 16 to

00:00:38.495 --> 00:00:41.842
29, with a generally favorable short-term

00:00:41.842 --> 00:00:42.400
prognosis.
